Photo:ICÂ At least ten people were killed Saturday in a bomb attack in the northern Syrian town of Al-Bab near the Turkish border, according to Turkish state-run Anadolu News agency.However, the Britain-based Syrian Observatory for Human Rights said at least 14 people were killed, including nine civilians.The blast reportedly happened when the bomb struck a bus and taxi station in the town.There's been no official confirmation on the death toll, and it's not immediately clear who carried out the attack.Al-Bab, 30 kilometers south of the Turkish border, is now controlled by the Turkish Army and its allied forces. 
